Package: jgd
Title: JSON Graphics Device
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Grant", "McDermott", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "contact@grantmcdermott.com")
Description: A graphics device that records R plotting operations and streams
    them as JSON over a Unix domain socket to an external renderer. The device
    acts as a pure recorder with no rendering dependencies â€” all rendering
    occurs in the client (e.g. a VS Code webview or any NDJSON-capable
    frontend).
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
NeedsCompilation: yes
Suggests: later
SystemRequirements: POSIX sockets (available on macOS, Linux; Windows support
    planned)
URL: https://github.com/grantmcdermott/jgd
BugReports: https://github.com/grantmcdermott/jgd/issues
